The paper deals with asymptotic enumeration and combinatorial invariants of families of codes, which are topics that are typically studied in information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses extremal properties of codes, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper uses techniques from numerical analysis (cs.NA) to derive precise asymptotic estimates.
